pageContext.claim: “The economy is doing really great. When you come back, you're going to see with the jobs and the companies coming back into our country....I especially like saying that companies are starting to come back.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump has made a habit of taking credit for business deals that were already in the works before he took office. Moreover, companies like Ford, GM, and Foxconn have moved some of their production to the U.S. as a result of market demands and long-term plans.
